      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE PREACHER (4) hasn't raced since a midfield finish in the G1 Breeders Crown 2CG Final five months ago at Melton but he won his lone fresh attempt and two recent trial wins suggest he has returned in fine order. Can make a winning return. PRETTYBOY HARRY (7) made it three minor placings from his past four starts when he raced parked but stuck on and finished 3 metres away in second in a higher-graded race last time out at Bendigo. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but he looks close to a win. THATS MY CARDIGAN (3) resumes after six months. Was still leaning at his maiden prep but showed ability in an easy maiden win at Maryborough and should have matured since. HILLWINSOME (2) came from the back row to finish second at Maryborough last start. A good draw can see him continue the good form.",
